This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Kristopher T. Hauenstein appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Larry R Pruden in court for Kristopher T. Hauenstein.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court by ADA Samuel Berg. Called @ 1:45 p.m. Appearances made. Matter before the Court for adjourned initial appearance, but Atty. is prepared to waive preliminary hearing and provides waiver to the Court. Defendant responds to Court's question regarding waiver and finds waiver to be freely, knowing, and intelligent. Discussion as to arraignment. State confirms charges in information will be the same as the criminal complaint. Based on that, Atty. Pruden enters not guilty pleas and asks that matter be set for the same date as other files. Court sets as requested and will update PSI writer as to this matter for the pre-sentence investigation on pending files.
Status conference scheduled for October 31, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Kristopher T. Hauenstein in court, in custody by video.  Attorney Larry R Pruden in court for Kristopher T. Hauenstein.  Attorney Vivien L. TenHaken in court for State of Wisconsin. Called @ 11:06 a.m. Appearances made. matter before the Court for plea hearing on 21CF409, 21CF411, 21CM595, and initial appearance on 22CF418. Called @ 3:13 p.m. Record by Atty. Pruden who is seeking to enter pleas on the older files, with PSI ordered. State agrees to have 22CF418 be part of sentencing once it goes through the process of initial appearance, preliminary hearing, and arraignment. Court sets newest file for adjourned initial appearance on August 23rd, and proceeds to take pleas on other matters.
Court goes over maximum penalties, deportation warnings. Defendant responds to Court's questions as to plea questionnaire. Atty. responds to questions of the Court as to entry of pleas and factual basis. 
Defendant pleads as follows:
GUILTY COUNT #1 IN 21CF411
GUILTY COUNT #2 IN 21CF409
GUILTY COUNT #1 IN 21CM595
ALL REMAINING COUNTS ARE DISMISSED AND READ IN.
Court finds pleas to be knowing, voluntary, intelligent, and finds defendant guilty.
Discussion as to PSI. Court will order PSI as requested in these matters, and sets all matters over to sentencing.  New file 22CF418 will track to sentencing as well. 
Court in recess.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for August 23, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
